<div class="ui container">
    <h3>Documentation:</h3>
    <div class="ui segment">
        <h3>Authentication</h3>
        <hr>

        <p>All API endpoints require an valid auth token. This auth token must be passed via the token for the HTTP Bearer scheme like so:<p>

        <div class="ui label"> <code>Authorization: Bearer $AUTH_TOKEN</code></div>

        <br><br>
    
        You can access all files for which you are the owner.

        <h3>Endpoints:</h3>
        <hr>

        <div class="ui raised segment">
            <b>Endpoint:</b> <b><code>/api/list/</code></b> 
            <br><br>
            <b>Description:</b> Lists all files.<br><br>
            <br> Example Request: 
            <code>
            <pre>
    curl "localhost:3000/api/list" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $AUTH_TOKEN"
            </pre>
            </code> 
        </div>
       
       <div class="ui raised segment">
           <b>Endpoint:</b> <b><code>/api/delete/:FILE_ID</code></b> 
           <br><br>
           <b>Description:</b> Deletes the file given by the FILE_ID.<br><br>
           Parameters:
           <table class="ui table">
               <thead>
                   <tr>
                       <th>Name</th>
                       <th>Type</th>
                       <th>Description</th>
                   </tr>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                   <tr>
                       <td><b><code>FILE_ID</code></b></td>
                       <td>string</td>
                       <td><b><code>_id</b></code> of the file to delete. Can be found using the <b><code>/api/list</b></code> endpoint.</td>
                   </tr>
               </tbody>
           </table>
           <br>
           <br> Example Request: 
           <code>
            <pre>
    curl -X DELETE "localhost:3000/api/delete/$FILE_ID" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $AUTH_TOKEN" \
            </pre>
            </code> 
       </div>

       <div class="ui raised segment">
           <b>Endpoint:</b> <b><code>/api/update/:FILE_ID</code></b> 
           <br><br>
           <b>Description:</b> Rename the file name and update description of the file given by the FILE_ID.<br><br>
           Parameters:
           <table class="ui table">
               <thead>
                   <tr>
                       <th>Name</th>
                       <th>Type</th>
                       <th>Description</th>
                   </tr>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                   <tr>
                       <td><b><code>FILE_ID</code></b></td>
                       <td>string</td>
                       <td><b><code>_id</b></code> of the file to delete. Can be found using the <b><code>/api/list</b></code> endpoint.</td>
                   </tr>
                   <tr>
                       <td><b><code>name</code></b></td>
                       <td>string</td>
                       <td>New name for the file</td>
                   </tr>
                   <tr>
                       <td><b><code>description</code></b></td>
                       <td>string</td>
                       <td>New description for the file</td>
                   </tr>
               </tbody>
           </table>
           <br>
           <br> Example Request: 
           <code>
            <pre>
    curl -X PUT "localhost:3000/api/update/$FILE_ID \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer $AUTH_TOKEN" \
      --form name="New Name" \
      --form description="New Description."
            </pre>
            </code> 
       </div>
       
    </div>
</div>
